license: wasi-libc (LICENSE beside this file — Apache-2.0-WITH-LLVM-exception /
         Apache-2.0 / MIT triple; the musl-derived pieces are MIT).

Why this is vendored: Ubuntu's `wasi-libc` apt package ships NO setjmp
(no header, no runtime), but LÖVE's FreeType dependency needs it
(smooth/ftgrays.c rasterizer, sfnt/ttcmap.c). wasm setjmp/longjmp is
implemented ON TOP OF wasm exception-handling (rt.c uses
__builtin_wasm_throw), so it rides on the exact standardized-EH machinery
this repo already builds — same encoding, same libc++abi.

Consumed by wasi/toolchain/build-libcxx-eh.sh, which installs the two
headers into $PREFIX/include and compiles rt.c (with the repo's EH flags)
to $PREFIX/lib/wasi-setjmp.o. Any TU that calls setjmp/longjmp is compiled
with $EH_FLAGS + $SJLJ_FLAGS (wasi/toolchain/eh-flags.sh) and links
wasi-setjmp.o. Witnessed by wasi/witness/sjlj-eh.cpp (setjmp + a C++ throw
in one module, node + Chromium + wasmtime). Update by replacing the three
files wholesale from a newer wasi-libc and refreshing this PIN. Never edit
in place.
